.TH "NODEITERATOR.WHATTOSHOW" "3JS" "October 23, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
NodeIterator.whatToShow \- NodeIterator: whatToShow property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]NodeIterator.whatToShow\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property
represents an \f[CR]unsigned integer\f[R] representing a bitmask
signifying what types of nodes should be returned by the
\f[CR]NodeIterator\f[R].
.SH VALUE
A non\-negative integer.
For the list of possible values, see
\f[CR]document.createNodeIterator()\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] nodeIterator = document.createNodeIterator(
  document.body,
  NodeFilter.SHOW_ELEMENT | NodeFilter.SHOW_COMMENT | NodeFilter.SHOW_TEXT,
  { acceptNode: (node) \f[B]=>\f[R] NodeFilter.FILTER_ACCEPT },
);
\f[B]if\f[R] (
  nodeIterator.whatToShow & NodeFilter.SHOW_ALL ||
  nodeIterator.whatToShow & NodeFilter.SHOW_COMMENT
) {
  \f[I]// nodeIterator will show comments\f[R]
}
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
The interface this property belongs to: \f[CR]NodeIterator\f[R].
